## Performance Characteristics

### Overhead in FAST Mode
- **Negligible**: Single Stopwatch.GetTimestamp() call at start/end
- **PerformanceCounter Query**: ~1-2ms (once per algorithm execution)
- **Memory Check**: ~0.1ms (GC query)
- **Total Overhead**: <5ms for most algorithms (imperceptible)

### Overhead in SLOW Mode
- **Minimal**: Same as FAST (measurement overhead is constant)
- **The observable slowdown is from Thread.Sleep() and screen refreshes** (intentional for visualization)
- **The system quantifies this overhead** via the SLOW vs FAST comparison

### Memory Impact
- **Per-Snapshot**: ~200 bytes (algorithm name, metrics, timestamp)
- **Per-Algorithm**: Average 5-10 snapshots = 1-2 KB
- **Total System**: ~50 KB for complete session (17 algorithms × 10 snapshots)
- **Negligible** compared to bitmap memory

